09/05/2006
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Serbian President Boris Tadic paid a surprise visit Monday (8 May) to Banja Luka, where he held closed-door meetings with Republika Srpska's leaders. Tadic separately met with Bosnian Serb counterpart Dragan Cavic, Prime Minister Milorad Dodik and BiH Foreign Minister Mladen Ivanic. The reported focus was on co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal, and on the unresolved cases of fugitives Ratko Mladic and Radovan Karadzic. (Dnevni avaz - 09/05/06; Tanjug - 08/05/06)
